Bitcoin Weekly Forecast Oct 30 Nov05 Key insights for the crypto market this week 2 27 weekly pump A gamechanger 2 Various scenarios we might encounter 3 Shifting stance quickly is a vital part of trading success Recap of last week In my last Bitcoin Weekly Forecast I acknowledged that the recent BTC pump exceeded my expectations I also emphasized the persistent rise of BTC dominance indicating its strength relative to ETH Altcoins and even SPX If BTC maintains its upward momentum and breaches the 32k 32k resistance zone we need to monitor the monthly resistance levels at 35k and 384k The price action unfolded impressively featuring a substantial green weekly candle from 299k to 352k considering the wick and a weekly close at 345k Though if we have a bearish stance we can argue that BTC closed at monthly resistance 35k it did surpass previous weekly resistance levels This 27 pump at this stage appears as a potential gamechanger introducing significant uncertainty into the mix Facing multiple scenarios ahead We will have a new BTC monthly candle in 2 days and this monthly close matters a lot 2If the monthly close is above 35k its super bullish with targets set at 372k 384k and the possibility of surging past 40k 2Monthly close between 32k 35k is bullish as well especially following a positive weekly close above 32k Avoiding a sharp drop in the next 2 days maintains the bullish outlook and we aim for the same targets as in Scenario 2 after a minor pullback 3Monthly close below 32k is bearish signaling a probable return to the previous range at 26k 28k So in summary the market may either pump with or without a shallow pullback leaving the sideliner away or experience a sharp drop confirming the recent pump as a trap for traders Either a upcoming pump or dump will be a big one People who expect a decent pull back to 30k to get in the car may not get a chance to do so Shifting stance quickly is a vital part of trading success To be honest Im currently taking a happy stance without a bias toward either bullish or bearish My trading setups will align with how BTCs price evolves Its crucial to highlight the importance of taking profits Three months ago I sold my spot BTC and shorted at 322k closing out at 258k I later repurchased spot and went long closing my long positions at 28k but Im still holding onto those spots You can track all these trades on my timeline Timely profittaking grants me flexibility when price action deviates slightly from expectations allowing for new trading setups In trading perfection isnt attainable What truly matters is how we adapt to different price movements If you enjoyed my forecasts and analysis please dont forget to Follow me for market insights on BTC crypto and stocks Like RT bookmark and drop a comment

Brazils USDT adoption is soaring in 2023 comprising a whopping 80 of all crypto transactions 
 
 USDT has seen a significant surge in adoption in Brazil accounting for 80 of all cryptocurrency transactions in the country so far in 2023
 
 As of midOctober USDT transactions in Brazil this year amounted to 272 billion Brazilian reais 55 billion almost double the volume of Bitcoin
 
 USDT transactions have been on the rise in Brazil since 2022 but crossed Bitcoin volume for the first time in July 2022 just at the peak of the crypto industrys storm last year when crypto lenders Three Arrows Capital and Voyager Capital collapsed
 
 The crypto winter slashed the volume of crypto transactions in the country by nearly 25 in 2022 ending at 2544 billion reais or 32 billion the government reported
 
 The Brazilian tax agency tracks cryptorelated activities of citizens using a sophisticated system that relies on artificial intelligence and network analysis According to a blog post the system is able to detect suspicious activity as well as trace the location of individuals trading cryptocurrencies
 
 The revenue agency is also targeting crypto investments held by the countrys citizens overseas On Oct 25 the local Congress passed legislation that recognizes cryptocurrencies as financial assets for tax purposes in foreign investments Earnings overseas between 6000 and 50000 reais 20000 will be subject to a 25 tax rate starting in January 2024 Above this threshold taxes will be applied at 225
 
 Since 2029 crypto exchanges operating in Brazil are required to disclose all user transactions to the government Capital gains from crypto sales exceeding 35000 reais 7000 per month are subject to a progressive tax bracket of 25 to 2250
 
 Global crypto exchanges such as Coinbase Binance Bitso and httpCryptocom operate in the country alongside local players such as Mercado Bitcoin and Foxbit

The Fee Market
 
 As the subsidy becomes replaced by the transaction fees the main source of revenue for the nodes becomes what we refer to as The Fee Market. Because bitcoin is meant for all, and for global use, it is illogical that the fee market would be comprised of large transaction fees.
 
 Large transaction fees price out large amounts of movement or spending of funds; the velocity of money slows to a snail's pace with high transaction fees. The majority of the world can not interact, trade, or connect with each other when the transaction fee is too large.
 
 To grow to global usage there must be micro-transactions so that everyone can transact. This is a key important element. At mass usage, with micro-transactions, the subsidy will easily be replaced and eclipsed by the transaction fees.

🖼️The big picture matters most. 🤔Are you informed on the big issues? Your macroeconomic update starts now 👇🧑‍🌾🎈Inflation Last year, inflation around the world reached multi-decade highs. Since then, it's been a major talking point for economists and #crypto enthusiasts alike. The good news is that many countries, including the United States, are potentially on the road to recovery. This month's CPI release showed U.S. consumer prices were unchanged in October, and the annual rise in underlying inflation was the smallest in two years. The United States hasn't been alone in its aggressive interest rate hikes to bring inflation under control over the last year and a half. The European Central Bank and the Bank of England also raised the cost of borrowing in a bid to curb severe inflation. - CPI has now dwindled from its peak in June last year to 3.2% - The S&P 500 turned in its best day since April and the Dow jumped almost 500 points on the news. 🌾Commodities According to the World Bank, commodity prices have been expected to fall this year and remain mostly stable throughout 2024. The outlier is rice, mostly because of supply shortages driven by India's cessation of non-basmati white rice exports in an effort to keep domestic prices affordable. Fertilizer prices are also expected to hover above historical averages due to supply constraints and China's current fertilizer export restrictions. - Agricultural prices are forecast to fall about 2% in 2024 and 2025 if unforeseen disruptions are avoided. - Food and beverage prices are expected to decline by about the same margin. - Raw agricultural materials could rise by over 1%. - Grains are also displaying their characteristic resistance to volatility, expected to pull back 4% on average in 2024 and 2025. Of course, these price predictions aren't able to take into account the persistence of geopolitical conflicts or the prolonging of ongoing ones, severe weather events (primarily driven by El Niño), or mass crop losses attributable to any number of causes. And the latest conflict in the Middle East has added to concerns for commodity markets. While we have yet to see drastic effects on prices and volatility materialize, conflicts in general (and especially those in oil-producing regions) have serious implications for potentially acute oil supply disruptions and, subsequently, world markets of all classes.
